radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled and dilated appendix measuring up to 10 mm, mild periappendiceal fat stranding, 4 mm probable appendicolith, clear lung bases, area of hypodensity within the liver likely representing focal fatty deposition, simple cyst in the right kidney, normal visualized loops of small and large bowel, trace amount of pelvic free fluid, no abscess, no free air, unremarkable spleen, pancreas, gallbladder, adrenal glands, left kidney, and uterus and adnexa.
